- Redesign the page structure for better usability and professional appearance.
- Enhance form input fields, preview section, and export buttons with consistent design.
- Ensure responsive layout for desktop, tablet, and mobile views.
- Improve user interactions (hover, focus, validation messages).

‚úÖ Acceptance Criteria

-  Users can toggle between light/dark themes seamlessly.
-  All text, buttons, and form elements remain readable and accessible in both themes.
-  The resume preview adapts correctly to theme changes.
-  Layout scales properly across different screen sizes.
-  UI aligns with modern design best practices.

Now, we will explore Copilot Edits, a feature that allows working more holistically on our repo. [Copilot - Edit Mode](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/copilot/copilot-edits) is an AI-powered code editing session to make changes across **multiple files** using **natural language**, and applies the edits directly in the editor, where you can review them in-place, with the full context of the surrounding code. #### Key features - **Multi-file Editing**: Copilot Edits can make changes across multiple files in your workspace. - **Iterative Workflow**: Designed for fast iteration, allowing you to review, accept, or discard AI-generated code. - **In-place Edits**: Shows generated code directly in your editor, providing a code review-like flow. - **Working Set**: Allows you to define which files the edits should be applied to. #### How it works 1. **Set Context**: Select files to be in the working set. 1. **Provide Instructions**: Use natural language to describe the required changes. 1. **Review Changes**: See proposed changes in-place in your code. 1. **Accept or Discard**: Review each suggested edit and choose which to keep. 1. **Iterate**: If needed, provide follow-up instructions to refine the changes. ### :keyboard: Activity: Use Copilot to add a new feature! :rocket: 1. If the Copilot Chat panel is not visible, please reopen it. 1. At the bottom of Copilot Chat window, use the dropdown to switch to **Edit** mode. 1. issue.title: Bug in queries with custom modules AND user defined collation
issue.body:
### Issue

Situation is very simple (I am talking about SuiteCRM 8.8.1 here, but it happened before in previous versions).

I have my suiteCRM 8.8.1 where all of my tables are defined as **utf8mb3_general_ci** collation (I do not recall when or where I have defined this or is this app default but that is the collation reported by phpmyadmin; I also do not know if I am able to change collation anywhere).

Now, in my SuiteCRM admin area (suitecrm/#/administration/Locale?view=default) I have defined **utfmb3_croatian_mysql561_ci** collation.

When I create custom module, it will create new module tables as **utfmb3_croatian_mysql561_ci** and as a result, when I go to module list view, it will create an background error and return empty list (if I go to the individual record through relationship, it will show up fine).

So, this is definetly a bug which happens if you have mismatch between collation defined for default tables vs. collation defined for a custom module.

### Possible Fix

Fix collation so that new tables will allways be created with default suitecrm collation OR fix list view query to allow lists made of joined tables of different collations (if possible).

Also, possible fix is that when you choose different collation in admin section/locale, you actually apply new collation to whole database.

### Steps to Reproduce the Issue

```bash
1.I have my suiteCRM 8.8.1 where all of my tables are defined as **utf8mb3_general_ci** collation (I do not recall when or where I have defined this or is this app default but that is the collation reported by phpmyadmin; I also do not know if I am able to change collation anywhere).

2. Now, in my SuiteCRM admin area (suitecrm/#/administration/Locale?view=default) I have defined **utfmb3_croatian_mysql561_ci** collation.

3. When I create custom module, it will create new module tables as **utfmb3_croatian_mysql561_ci** and as a result, when I go to module list view, it will create an background error and return empty list (if I go to the individual record through relationship, it will show up fine).

4. When I go to list view of my new module, it will not return list of records and will also not report an error.
```

### Context

I have installed SuiteCRM and later on changed collation in order to follow my national alphabet (and special characters).

### Version

8.8.1

### What browser are you currently using?

Firefox

### Browser Version

latest

### Environment Information

php 8.3.24, 10.11.11-MariaDB-0

### Operating System and Version

+deb12u1 - Debian 12
